{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"57b2674c-6a3b-4842-9b14-f5e90f19acb8","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types defined in files listed *before* them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but is listed first.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_LkXOGwFWwgKc1RvOWCiuMF","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-fb7b7dffd01e4cda90419808f64c83f4/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-fb7b7dffd01e4cda90419808f64c83f4/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"35047a95-0a72-4347-b891-329c3731f5cf","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference types/modules defined in files that appear *before* them in the compilation order. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` (listed first) — depends on `BrokenOrder.Domain` (opens it)\n2. `Domain.fs` (listed second) — defines `BrokenOrder.Domain`\n3. `Program.fs` (listed third) — depends on both\n\nThe problem is that `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` has `open BrokenOrder.Domain`. Since `Domain.fs` hasn't been compiled yet at that point, this fails.\n\n\nThe solution is straightforward: I need to reorder the files in the project so `Domain.fs` compiles first, followed by `Services.fs`, then `Program.fs`.","outputTokens":484,"requestId":"7C18:B515D:B39973:CC3171:6A0279A9"},"id":"8921479d-4894-4def-9869-0aa515f1b130","timestamp":"2026-05-12T00:52:01.595Z","parentId":"f0ca073b-e636-4b8b-b007-11df83363957"}
